title: For Sale/Trade:  1939 Tula 91/30, Winchester Model 12 built 1929, Belgian Flobert Parlor Rifle
postcontent:
I have three long guns up for sale and I will be at the Washington County Gun Show on Saturday, June 20. I will have all three with me on that day. 

The first is just your standard Mosin Nagant 91/30, but an especially nice specimen. This is a 1939 Tula, and is in a proper pre-war stock with the screwed-in sling escutcheons. This is a great shooter, and a keeper. Already cleaned of Cosmolene, and ready for your collection. If if you are going to own one round receiver Mosin Nagant, this one is to be considered. I am 200 firm on the Mosin. 

The second is a Winchester Model 12 built 1929. The more desirous 16 gauge. It is the 2 3/4 full choke. Great patina, and includes the authentic Winchester 5 round plug for the tubular magazine. I am absolutely hard knock on 400 for this shotgun, and not negotiable. Will include about a dozen rounds as well. I do not wish to sell this shotgun, but I would like a left hand flintlock more. 

Lastly is a gun you don't see every day. This little rifle is a Belgian Flobert Parlor Rifle. This does not fire the 22 short, it fires the 6mm Flobert, or 22 CB Cap ammunition. Likely built prior to 1900. This particular specimen was in a collection for many years, and had a rimfire scope soldered onto the gun. I had a gunsmith remove the scope mount, and now this is a great piece. The bore is worn but shiny, and this will be a great addition to any collection. Asking 250 for the rifle. 

Again, I will be at the Washington County (PA) Gun Show on Saturday, June 20. I am shopping and selling that day. Please do not hesitate to contact me at Seven24 Nine9One 88FiveThree. I text like a teenager. 

Thanks!   Prof

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 40-RARE $375.00 OBO
location: Lake Wylie,SC/Gastonia, NC, Charlotte, North Carolina
postcontent: With a long spring recoil auto-load system like the Browning A5, this model Winchester was patterned after the famed Winchester Model 1911SL, “Widowmaker”. Unlike the 1911SL, the Model 40 is not designed to manual load by manually sliding the barrel by hand. This was Winchester’s second attempt at a self-loader. They made approx. 12,000 of them only during the years 1940-1941. Winchester placed a recall on them and sent people who traded them in a brand new Model 12. Consequently, many were taken out of existence and destroyed leaving a limited number out there with people who chose not to trade them in. So, numbers are low and consequently, appreciated by Winchester collectors and the like. This Model 40 is in very nice condition and it has a Full Choke. Serial number #28_6 so it is a first year.  I will consider trades REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Voodoo tactical Tobago pack in ACU pattern
postcontent:
This Tobago Large Pack from Voodoo Tactical is a great piece of equipment that competes with the CamelBak BFM and similar packs that sell for more than $200. Honestly, we think this is a steal at this price. It has all sorts of clever accouterments and extra touches, such as Velcro covers for the hydration tube passage and tie down straps in the main compartment.
The pack itself is 20" x 19" (at the widest point) x 12" with two large pockets on the back and two additional pocket on each side. If that isn't enough space, you can add to it using the many MOLLE PAL attachment points. It also features internal pockets, two radio pouches and room for two hydration bladders of three liters each (you can add more hydration carriers in the main compartment or externally, if you wish). The thickly padded adjustable shoulder and sternum straps can be removed to convert the pack to a carry-all by using the top and side nylon carry handles. Fully covered zippers with pulls, bottom bedroll loops and side compression straps to secure your load.
The pack is surprisingly comfortable under heavy loads, with body-contoured shoulder straps, a sternum strap with lumbar support and a waist belt. It has an aluminum and polymer internal frame to add structure and also has individual back panels to promote maximum air flow, keeping you cooler.
The Tobago Large Assault pack is as big or bigger than many three-day assult packs, but we think it holds enough to last most of us much longer in the field.
